          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A Comparison of the Gamma-Ray Spectra from 2.8-keV",
                " Neutron Capture and Thermal-Neutron Capture in",
                " Sodium-23."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Reactor CP-5."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Reactor core with a flux ~3E+13 n.cm**2.s**(-1)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Reactor spectrum filtered with a boron-10 shield."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "14.6-g sodium sample in zirconium metal container",
                " surrounded by a 0.5-in.-thick layer of 10B."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Internal-target arrangement used so that the sample",
                " (capture-gamma-ray source) was located in the",
                " high-flux region of a reactor and was viewed (through",
                " a collimator) by a detector located outside of the",
                " reactor. The 2.8-keV resonance was selectively",
                " populated by using the boron-shielded target",
                " technique."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BPAIR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " High-resolution annihilation pair spectrometer."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 14N(n,gamma)15N reaction (with nitrogen introduced",
                " in the tube) was used as a calibration standard for",
                " both the relative intensities and the energies.",
                "Absolute intensities obtained by normalization to well-",
                " known 2.754-MeV gamma line following the beta decay",
                " of 24Na."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Absolute intensities corrected for self-absorption in",
                " the sodium sample."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical errors given; in the peak areas",
                " these are expected to dominate the systematic errors",
                " and fit errors."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "E-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Estimated systematic uncertainty in gamma-ray",
                " energy; function of the errors in the energies of the",
                " standard nitrogen lines and errors in determining the",
                " centroids of the unknown sodium lines."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The hypothesis that a bound level contributes to the",
                " thermal-neutron capture cross section was tested by",
                " comparing the resonance spectrum with the thermal-",
                " neutron capture gamma-ray spectrum: Departure from",
                " complete correlation between the absolute intensities",
                " of lines in the two spectra was used as a measure of",
                " the contribution of the bound level to the thermal-",
                " capture cross section."
              ]
            }
          ],
